text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i‚Äôve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i‚Äôm about to go back, knowing what i know, and we‚Äôre about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump‚Äôs election, trumpeted the return of their ‚Äúpopulist hero‚Äù on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication‚Äôs announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there‚Äôs any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i‚Äôm leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents ‚Äì on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
ho fatto questa illustrazione per la casa delle donne @luchaysiesta .

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
there is a healing power in creative expression. 
yesterday i had a papsmeer. when you've had a very crappy childhood sexual abuse experience certain things are painful triggers.. this was definitely one of them.
our bodies store memories physically, muscle memory. the flood of memories and bodily sensations can be as traumatic as the original incident. they threaten to overwhelm and capsize you with the intensity of each wave/flood of memory.

i always yearn to cut it out, cut myself open and just pour out the painful sensations so they cannot take up space in my skin my body my heart my soul and their permanent residence;my mind!

art has become this escape, i'll mindlessly or frantically pick up my materials and put every unnamed, unprocessed, unsure emotion onto paper. i cannot always verbalise the feelings. but the paper willingly takes them, holds them and transforms them from murky, dark, fearbased anxiety into a form i can recognise.

i was too young and vulnerable to understand what was happening, my adult self breaks to pieces with each intrusive memory, desperate to shield my child self from the horrors no child should even know exists.

complex post traumatic shock syndrome (no longer classed as a disorder but a symptom of trauma) is manageable. it is brutal. it can feel overwhelming beyond measure but your mind can heal from those brutal wounds. we might limp slightly but broken bones heal stronger and broken souls heal fiercer!

text:
life after|i am so blessed to say that my article, titled ‚Äúlife after sexual abuse‚Äù has been published in injoy magazine @crystal_injoy_magazine !!! it‚Äôs a blessing to be able to share parts of my story to help someone else. here is an excerpt from the publication...‚Äùi was 11 years old visiting a close relatives house with my immediate family. i found myself  in the back room of the house alone; one of the young men enters the room & sat me on his lap. i didn‚Äôt really think nothing of it because i knew this family member very well with no prior issues. he proceeded to cover my ear stick his tongue in it while touching & rubbing on me inappropriately. instantly; i became numb, i felt ashamed and i was afraid. it lasted about 5-10 mins but it seemed like forever. he took me off his lap and i couldn‚Äôt comprehend what just happened to me! i didn‚Äôt know what to do. i felt frozen in fear! in that moment, i decided to not tell anyone. i just kept it to myself. before particular incident happened, i had already been sexually abused starting at the age of 5 by other young men. as i got older; i felt the shame of it, the pain from it and started to feel like i didn‚Äôt belong. i was angry at my abusers and wanted to know why they would do this to me. why would they violate my body.‚Äù thank you so much to ms. crystal for this opportunity! a special thanks to @kid.august for taking very beautiful photos that help tell my story, to my sissy @iamsarahmatthews for the wonderful design layout and to @oldmillcafe_ec for the eclectic location for the shoot! #tellyourstory #beyondthebarriers of #depression there is #hope

text:
don‚Äôt just aspire to make a living. .

aspire to make a difference. .

i spent 20 years working my tail off in the las vegas real estate market,  and my husband and i made a great living. .

it afforded us choices and one was to retire and pursue a chance to make a difference. .

often times we don‚Äôt even know how one person can do that.  but it‚Äôs the little‚Äôs acts of kindness that creates the ripple effect of change we are seeking in the world. .

now, a smile or a kind gesture isn‚Äôt going to fix all of our worlds problems but it just may change one persons day. .

look at that. you already started to make a difference! .

i challenge you to start putting the wheels in motion to aspire to make a difference anyway you can.

i was walking my children to school early morning, when a group of working men in a building site started whistling at me and making sexual noises. one of them shouted come on turn around love, don't be shy we don't bite. i was horrified that certain men think that this behaviour is acceptable. my poor children had to witness the filth that was said to me. these individuals choose a time when they know a woman is vulnerable and won't be able to fight back.

to make matters worse, when i explained to a friend what had happened she replied saying oh don't worry babe it's because your pretty, don't take no notice of it.

.

text:
here‚Äôs the reality: most sexual assaults and sexual violence are perpetrated by men, and arise within asymmetrical power dynamics. the aggressor occupies a more powerful or dominant position in relation to the victim. 
the vast majority of #metoo stories describe occurrences where men assert power bestowed on them by simply being a man. from homes to bars to school to state houses across the country to the white house, the stories we‚Äôve all survived involve powerful, prominent men who use their positions and the perks of their power to seduce, coerce, manipulate, and attack. 
these men have what victims, who are in less powerful positions, want and need: a job, good grades, a promotion, a recommendation, an audition, a role in a movie, a place close to the center of power. they confuse and control by dangling enticements with one hand and wielding threats, implied or explicit, with the other. 
sexual abuse is all about power. we won‚Äôt stop calling attention to rape culture and those who benefit from it until it no longer exists.

text:
‚óΩ‚óΩ‚óΩ‚óΩ‚óΩswipe üëà 
please read üëâdowned cow: the true story of one anonymous animal born into the meat industry
the truck carrying this cow was unloaded one september morning. after the other animals were removed from the truck, she was left behind, unable to move. the stockyard workers used their customary electric prods in her ear to try to get her to move, then beat and kicked her in the face, ribs, and back but still she couldn't move. they tied a rope around her neck, tied the other end to a post in the ground and drove the truck away. the cow was dragged along the floor of the truck and fell to the ground, landing with both hind legs and her pelvis broken. she remained like that until 7:30 that evening.
_
for the first three hours, she lay in the hot sun crying out. periodically, when she urinated or defecated, she used her front legs to drag herself along the gravel to a clean spot. she also tried to crawl to a shaded area but couldn't move far enough. altogether, she managed to crawl a painful 13 to 14 yards. the stockyard employees wouldn't allow her any drinking water.
_
at 4:30 p.m. three dogs were attacking the cow who was still alive. she had suffered a number of bite wounds. the stockyard workers would not euthanize her, claiming that in order to preserve the value of meat, she could not be destroyed. the butcher eventually arrived at 7:30 p.m. and shot her. her body was purchased for $307.50
_
now you know. the question is what will you do? every bite of animal products that you take involves fear, cruelty, immense suffering, pain and death. ask yourself when you can not only survive but thrive on a plant-based diet, why wouldn't you?

pope francis has publicly acknowledged for the first time that there is a problem of priests and even bishops sexually abusing nuns in the roman catholic church. after he was asked to comment on the issue during a news conference aboard a plane returning to rome from a trip to the united arab emirates, the pope admitted that the issue is ongoing and said that they must do more to fight the problem. in recent years, catholic nuns in india, africa, latin america, and italy have accused clerics of sexual abuse, and a vatican magazine last week mentioned nuns having abortions or giving birth to the children of priests, according to the new york times. (üìπ: reuters)

text:
red once bled into the painful memories of my past. you can easily lose hope in life when your innocence was taken away at such a young age and when you are continuously reminded that you should have been aborted. the pure rage that was beaten upon my fragile little body revived an inner strength unlike no other. and through it all i still have undying hope for my parents because of the power of forgiveness. faith will do that to you.¬†red. the color of love.

text:
it is a true honor to score for this series of animated shorts for #metoo movement. the videos, which were screened at the sundance film festival 2019. while working on this. by hearing those survivors voices, i can really feel their pain and loneliness. there are so many others in the world needs our support. i'm so grateful that i can do something. we can all do this, support survivors and end sexual violence.

text:
sometimes we do too!
.
it‚Äôs so easy to get overwhelmed and feel like you‚Äôve got too much to do. we often get so caught up thinking about the things we have to do, we end up getting too stressed to do anything! the more we add to our mental list, the more we stress, the less we do, the more the list grows and so on, and so on.
.
so how do you get out of that cycle of overwhelm? <cue thunder and lightning>
.
here‚Äôs what i do.
.
first, take a breathe, and write a list of everything you‚Äôve got to get done.  get rid of the mental list. things are a lot less scary when they‚Äôre written down.
.
start eliminating the things that aren‚Äôt urgent or important. .
then eliminate things that you can ask somebody else to do. contrary to popular belief, you don‚Äôt have to do everything yourself! this is a huge bug bear for me because i‚Äôm a huge control freak but i have learnt to accept that whilst someone else might not do something exactly the same way i would have, it‚Äôs still good enough.
.
pick, at max, 3 most urgent and important things on your list and schedule them in for today. those are the only things you need to get done today!
.
this is probably the hardest and most important step‚Ä¶..
.
focus on one thing at a time.
.
think about nothing other than the task you‚Äôre doing until it‚Äôs complete. .
this is definitely easier said than done, and it takes practice!!
.
do this for your three tasks and then don‚Äôt worry about anything else for the rest of the day!
.

it‚Äôs so easy to get overwhelmed and feel like you‚Äôve got too much to do. we often get so caught up thinking about the things we have to do, we end up getting too stressed to do anything! the more we add to our mental list, the more we stress, the less we do, the more the list grows and so on, and so on.
.
so how do you get out of that cycle of overwhelm? <cue thunder and lightning>
.
here‚Äôs what i do.
.
first, take a breathe, and write a list of everything you‚Äôve got to get done.  get rid of the mental list. things are a lot less scary when they‚Äôre written down.
.
start eliminating the things that aren‚Äôt urgent or important. .
then eliminate things that you can ask somebody else to do. contrary to popular belief, you don‚Äôt have to do everything yourself! this is a huge bug bear for me because i‚Äôm a huge control freak but i have learnt to accept that whilst someone else might not do something exactly the same way i would have, it‚Äôs still good enough.
.

text: @itsjen.nyc and i went to the opera last night! it was my first time there, the building it extraordinary. would highly rec everyone go, rush tix are $25! we saw don giovanni, good pic for a first opera (legendary, breezy, silly, easy to follow) but truly bizarre in the #metoo era. don is cringy at it's hard to tell if this production wants us to sympathize with him, or understand why he does what he does. tbh i don't understand the character at all, or why this would be staged without consideration for the current climate. very strange. opera, dude!

text:
hi nudies! dear prudence here. i'm in a couple of #metoo conversations with friends atm and it's at once bleak yet filling me with hope. so i thought to extend the discourse to our community.
.

i'd like to reinstate #sundaynvdestalks this sunday with exactly that: an thread of stories of how the #metoo movement has shaped / is shaping our relationships now.
.
we know that the topic can be very triggering for some, so you can opt not to join the convo. it would be a very delicate exchange so we enjoin everyone to maintain the sacredness and safety of our space as we talk about our experiences.
.

text:
peanut, the state's top liberal schnauzer with a long, exalted history of public service, is accused by number of female dogs of unwanted sexual advances.

the revelations came amid a political crisis in virginia. gov. ralph northam and attorney general mark. r. herring said they dressed in blackface decades ago, and lt. gov. justin e. fairfax is accused of sexual assault.

a number of female dogs, among them schnauzers and other breeds, accuse peanut of sexual assault, including many unwanted sexual advances.

a few of the accusers say peanut licked them without consent, and was inappropriately suggestive. ‚Äúpeanut don‚Äôt treat his bitches well,‚Äù said richmond resident david stanton. ‚Äúi see him carousing out in the park all the time as if he owns the place and every dog in it.‚Äù authorities are investigating the charges, but in the meantime peanut has been prohibited from public spaces.

#blackface #metoo #dog #dogsofinstagram #dogs #virginia #politics #democrats #republicans #scandal #racism #blm

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
my healing process involves a lot of writing.

growing up in a culture that undervalues intuition and subtle senses, not learning how to claim them for myself, it was easy to push down and ignore feelings, to sing them aside for what my culture told me would prove my worth.

like a relationship. even one that i knew from the beginning didn't feel right. my mind could easily find ways to convince me to stay, that the only worth i would find as a woman would be wrapped up in a man's arms.

my healing process involves writing my feelings. my anger, confusion, sadness and regret. validating those feelings and making them real.

my healing process also involves pouring through old journals, seeking to understand myself, to remember the feelings and dreams that got lost under trauma recycled into another relationship.

as i was reading last night, i decided there is a lot i want to share. i want to make it all real for me again, so that i can find strength in my senses to not let them slip past my awareness again.

my story is not linear, and i do not intend to tell it as such, but it will flow as follows. "he took advantage of me. he saw in me something that he wanted, and he did whatever he could to take it. he lied, manipulated, sweet talked, and controlled the situation to have me dropping my boundaries, my faith, and my gut instincts so that i'd let him in.

so he took me, and i was too confused to say no. i surrendered, in a twisted way, to his will and i let myself be pulled into his grasp. he claimed my body because i hadn't, and couldn't.

satisfied with his fill, he released his hold enough for me to feel my skin, raw from his touch. i felt my heart, wounded by betrayal, and i sank into a river of tears for the violation to my spirit.

my eyes burned with the pain of losing sight of my power - seeing only how i'd let my body be used for his gain. i felt weak for the self-sacrifice, feeling that truly i was nothing more than property for him to set his sights on to conquer and own.

my value for my own worth was reflected clearly, and i took it as a sign of truth, rather than seeing it for the hateful love that it was." ~rhea heartsong~
feb 5/19
name: ~ Rhea Lazuli Melia ~

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
#refecttorenew #day 5 guided #writing @weareselfcentered
‚úçüèæembarrassing to admit, at 29 most of my life has felt like a major struggle just to have an equitable and enjoyable quality of life experience. from being bullied/terrorized for the entirety of grade school until graduation, to being adopted, to dealing with parents‚Äô divorce, to having to work from the age of 14‚Äìthrough college and graduate education, to a list of failed, toxic relationships. on many days, i have found myself weary from the weight and burdens of significant trauma. i can feel my body shrink and cave in under the pressure.
to relieve myself from this feeling the quickest healing is to breathe deeply and slowly
üßòüèæ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è my herstory is one of the reasons i am firmly committed to doing the spiritual self-development work necessary to permanently shift outdated paradigms and reboot my brain to manifest ease, joy, abundance, love, and success. üëçüèΩ
one recent challenge i have overcome is navigating a series of mini-housing crises since a #metoo incident in 2012 radically changed my life course. this saga lasted over 8 years and sent my life journey down a vastly different trajectory than the perfect picture i had once envisioned. an abusive ivy-league ex boyfriend cheated on me multiple times and his encore presentation...was to set me up to be sexually assaulted and humiliated in front of him by the woman he played me with. both of them admitted (at the time of the incident) to the situation being premeditated and planned in advance by them. this situation spiraled further out of control when that same ex came to my apartment in santa monica, ca around the thanksgiving break holiday to attempt to apologize and repair our relationship. üôÖüèæ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è
the incident ended with an ivy-league educated man attempting to hit me with his car, the police arriving threatening to take only me to jail, since he was long gone by the time they arrived, me experiencing muteness and an inability to speak and express for about 1.5 months, and ‚Äúa series of unfortunate events‚Äù in multitude afterwards. this ushered shame in my life because it directly impacted my financial well-being and my brain continue-in comments üëâ

text:
memories: 2001 found this little gem cleaning out my art studio yesterday. i think it‚Äôs ok to look back and see what was with wiser eyes. important though, to look gently and with a heart full of love. see what was with acceptance, and maybe be open to new insights. i see my children now, from a distance‚Ä¶i see how little, gentle and delicate they were, but surprisingly too, i see how vulnerable i was. how much i wanted support, to feel love and to be seen. i‚Äôm glad i didn‚Äôt know then the immense struggles i would have - but to name them here and now - would be to call them back to me. by knowing what was/is true and standing in the light, i have survived and thrived ... and so have they. 
as i have been finding my way to finally being comfortable in my own skin, they are naturally blossoming into brilliant, creative, authentic people. so much pride. so much love...for us all. üíõüíú‚ù§Ô∏è
#onelove #mothers #metoo #innerintegration #narcissisticabuse #ancestors #legacy 
#traumarecovery #posttraumaticgrowth #sacredfeminine #goddess #divinefeminine

text:
#metoo: accusing repeatedly without formal complaint is not authentic, says kailash kher
#
mumbai: singer kailash kher, who has been accused by multiple women of sexual harassment, says that in his view, if a person is not making a formal complaint and just continues to accuse, it is not authentic. kailash was interacting with the media at the music launch of marathi film "dokyala shot" along with riteish deshmukh and abhijit panse here. a few months ago, singer sona mahapatra had shared her alleged unsavoury experience with kailash, and after that, at least four other women raised allegations against the "teri deewani" singer. sona, in an interview, has said she will not lodge a police complaint against kailash, but she will make sure he doesn't repeat his alleged act in future. kailash kherreacting to this, kailash said: "everyone has their own thinking. if i accuse someone only by taking that individual's name over and over again then, nothing will come out of it. if you will take legal recourse against that person, then it becomes another matter altogether. "if i tell you that i will not make a complaint against that individual, but still i will accuse him of doing certain criminal activity, then i feel it's not an authentic complaint." does he‚Ä¶

text:
i constantly remind myself how strong my emotions can be. perhaps what i label as love is something else, something so sinister and powerful that everytime it leaves, it turns my life upside down. so sometimes i tell myself, i will stay quiet. i will confine myself to the four walls in my room. i will look out the window when people talk. i will shut myself up when i feel. i will not listen to my heart. whenever i feel the need to be loved and known, i will do the opposite of what gets me there. when i'm in love i will treat it with indifference until it dries, its roots, and dies a ghostly death. 
i will make myself invisible.
name: Writings Of An Unstable Mind

text:
calling all girls and women! 
be in control of your personal safety! 
would you like the skill and knowledge to know what to do and how to react if faced with an aggressor? 
to feel safe and confident when travelling, going out or with a young child. 
this course will help you take those steps. taught by someone who had to take them herself. 
this is self defence course specifically designed to tackle the types of violent situations women and girls are like to face. 
learn how to use what you have to your advantage. ‚Äúovercoming fear is one of the biggest struggles even for women who train, this is one of the topics we will be covering. we want to ensure the women who attend leave equipped with strong mental attitude and how to tune into their own ability to survive as well as a physical skill set‚Äù sifu della 
physical, mental and internal training is what our course is offering. 
sifu della knows first hand how frightening and disabling it can be to face a dangerous person who can very easily overpower you. 
she will be sharing her experience and has written the program based on that understanding and her years of training martial arts and self empowerment. 
offering 5 free spaces to women who are experiencing or have experiences some form of harassment or violence in their lives! inbox to secure place. 
link in bio to book for the course

text:
truth!
‚ô°
if we really want to love we must learn how to forgive.
‚ô°
that includes forgiving others, even for the unthinkable, and forgiving ourselves, even for the unthinkable!
‚ô°
it‚Äôs not always easy to forgive.
‚ô°
when my coach gave me an assignment to write a letter to the person that repeatedly sexually abused my body and find compassion for him i felt a lot of resistance inside because i really didn‚Äôt want to do the assignment. (i didn‚Äôt have to mail it or give it to him. i just needed to write it.) but i was paying her to coach me and push me out of my comfort zone. i reminded myself of a mantra that struck a chord with me when i heard tony robbins at one of his seminars belt it out in his deep commanding voice: ‚Äúif you can‚Äôt, you must‚Äù, so i begrudgingly started writing.
‚ô°
that letter was just the start of the forgiveness process for me. it wasn‚Äôt until two years later and after i completed numerous intense therapy sessions, cried an abundance of tears, and experienced countless ah-ha‚Äôs, that i was ready to genuinely forgive him. not because someone told me to, not because that‚Äôs what i was supposed to do, but because i was ready to let go. ‚ô°
forgiveness is a process, and we must learn it if we really want to love.
.
.
.
.
.
#learnhowtoforgive #motherteresa#forgivnessheals #forgivenessisaprocess #metoo #metoomovement #othersideofmetoo #tonyrobbins #ifyoucantyoumust

text:
i am running this course in just over a week. ‚Äî‚Äî
calling all girls and women! 
be in control of your personal safety! 
would you like the skill and knowledge to know what to do and how to react if faced with an aggressor? 
to feel safe and confident when travelling, going out or with a young child. 
this course will help you take those steps. taught by someone who had to take them herself. 
this is self defence course specifically designed to tackle the types of violent situations women and girls are like to face. 
learn how to use what you have to your advantage. ‚Äúovercoming fear is one of the biggest struggles even for women who train, this is one of the topics we will be covering. we want to ensure the women who attend leave equipped with strong mental attitude and how to tune into their own ability to survive as well as a physical skill set‚Äù sifu della 
physical, mental and internal training is what our course is offering. 
sifu della knows first hand how frightening and disabling it can be to face a dangerous person who can very easily overpower you. 
she will be sharing her experience and has written the program based on that understanding and her years of training martial arts and self empowerment. 
offering 5 free spaces to women who are experiencing or have experiences some form of harassment or violence in their lives! inbox to secure place. 
link in bio to book for the course 
picture credit @dougsouthall

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
i did what i had to do to survive. as i healed from abuse in seeking what i thought was self care i taught myself to indulge myself with food and reward myself with unhealthy behaviour. as a woman i was taught to put everyone first before myself. however this did not help this just taught me to internalize and neglect myself. . 
years of therapy taught me that i could take time to myself. that i needed to start saying no if did not serve me or my family first. last year was a big year of healing for me. first came my emotional and spiritual self. my learning to treat myself how i deserved to be treated. after came the residual hurt that had manifested in my body and every symptom that pointed to fibromyalgia had me defeated. i refused to believe that was what the rest of my life would look. i truly learned that: "self-care is not an indulgence. self-care is a discipline. it requires tough-mindedness, a deep and personal understanding of your priorities, and a respect for both yourself and the people you choose to spend your life with." https://bit.ly/2uokpux
.
i decided it was time to really care for myself and started by focusing on my nutrition and my bathroom cabinet went from 6rx to help me deal and cope with ptsd to a vitalizing plan. i was used to the side effects the anxiety, depression and pain medication had given me. i accepted them as being normal. so when the vitalizer plan started to renew my body i was not sure what to do with all the well being that it brought me. after taking those rx for about 7 years, i find myself grateful to to go to bed and not have to take my meds. vitalizing plan and self care has heal me from anxiety, depression, and i dare to say fibromyalgia!
.
whatever you do take time for yourself today, read a book, mediate. just say no to what others are asking you to do and do something just for yourself! .

name: Lisseth West
tweet_full:
i did what i had to do to survive. as i healed from abuse in seeking what i thought was self care i taught myself to indulge myself with food and reward myself with unhealthy behaviour. as a woman i was taught to put everyone first before myself. however this did not help this just taught me to internalize and neglect myself. . 
years of therapy taught me that i could take time to myself. that i needed to start saying no if did not serve me or my family first. last year was a big year of healing for me. first came my emotional and spiritual self. my learning to treat myself how i deserved to be treated. after came the residual hurt that had manifested in my body and every symptom that pointed to fibromyalgia had me defeated. i refused to believe that was what the rest of my life would look. i truly learned that: "self-care is not an indulgence. self-care is a discipline. it requires tough-mindedness, a deep and personal understanding of your priorities, and a respect for both yourself and the people you choose to spend your life with." https://bit.ly/2uokpux
.
i decided it was time to really care for myself and started by focusing on my nutrition and my bathroom cabinet went from 6rx to help me deal and cope with ptsd to a vitalizing plan. i was used to the side effects the anxiety, depression and pain medication had given me. i accepted them as being normal. so when the vitalizer plan started to renew my body i was not sure what to do with all the well being that it brought me. after taking those rx for about 7 years, i find myself grateful to to go to bed and not have to take my meds. vitalizing plan and self care has heal me from anxiety, depression, and i dare to say fibromyalgia!
.
whatever you do take time for yourself today, read a book, mediate. just say no to what others are asking you to do and do something just for yourself! .

text:
first things first, i‚Äôm okay.. i‚Äôm not in a dark place right now. but there will never be a right time to post this. i won‚Äôt delve too far into it. i will let you know this: this is truly a personal experience and i‚Äôve struggled to come to terms with this over the years. i‚Äôve struggled to admit that it happened. i still do but it did. and i live with it and i grow and evolve from it. i put on a brave face but i‚Äôm still scared. nowadays, i‚Äôll be perfectly fine, living the best life possible. but that‚Äôs not always the case for everyone. i‚Äôm in a better place now, although there will be times where the memories will randomly hit me. 
sexual violence victims/sufferers should not have to feel alone or feel ashamed. the purpose of #metoo is to #empower women and men, who are victims of #sexualharrassment and violence, through #empathy. the #purpose is to give #courage and #strength to stand up and face your attacker. the #metoomovement is to let you know that you do not have to fight this on your own. 
lastly, only a couple people closest to me know about it. this isn‚Äôt something that i told everyone, even though it is about to be known to whoever is reading this. i don‚Äôt want any of you to worry or wonder but be educated in a way. you or someone you know has experienced sexual harassment/violence. 
#personal #confession #words #poetry

text:
before you released¬†lust for life¬†in 2017, you¬†released a trailerfor the album, and you talked about how the music was a reflection of transitioning from one era to another. was it any different this time around? did you feel like you were still in that transitional period, or in a completely different space?

ldr:¬†"yes and no. i think my biggest surprise is that i expected to feel like i was out of that transition. we're a couple years into the presidency and a couple of years into some of the cultural and political destruction we've all been experiencing. #metoo is a year and a half old. we've got a lot of [huge changes]. i think i'm always expecting to wake up at the beginning of january and feel like a brand new person, and the same with the record. i'm always expecting to be the next version of myself by the time i'm done.
actually i am feeling like there has been a continued shift throughout this record, but not in the way i thought it would be. i think i wait for this "aha" moment to dawn upon me, and things don't really work like that. growth doesn't always happen in a straight line. it's not like you wake up one day, and you're like, "now i'm gonna do disco!" and i'm a new genre. it's more like, progress is back and forth and i think it's just having the willingness to want, for me. my goal is for things to be really safe and serene and fun, just in my own personal life and in my music. for my music, my aspirations are for things to get deeper and smarter, and if the melodies can still be beautiful then that's a cherry on top for sure. they all of go hand-in-hand. they all sort of happen at the same time."

whether it's an industrial #dairy farm or a small scale, organic farm, the process to produce #breastmilk is the same: a young female #cow is continually, artificially, and forcefully inseminated to produce a calf who is then torn away from her shortly after birth so that her milk can be sold to humans instead. when she can no longer keep up with the quantity of #milk demand placed on her, she will be slaughtered (at a fraction of her natural life-span) and ground into low-grade #hamburger.

text:
thursday thoughts üí≠

a staggering 98% of music industry producers are men and 97% of music industry engineers/mixers are men. lets get #womeninthemix. so when people say that the music industry is male dominated, it definately comes from somewhere! 
patriarchal culture is still real across the music industry and the #metoo movement has clarified that some women have been targeted by these men due to their positions and misogyny, causing a hierarchical stature in the industry where this power has been abused.

this has occured in different ways stemming from a lack of respect towards female co-workers, from women earning less and feeling unheard, to cases of sexual assault and harassment, where unfortunately the perpetrators in power have managed to maintain their jobs. thanks to #metoo, some women have begun to find liberation from these situations but others are still fighting hard to make changes in the scene.

more men need to become aware of the reality of this and invite, introduce and welcome more women into the music industry with open arms and a supportive nature. some women may even feel intimidated by such figures or feel belittled by some. no matter which gender you identify with, we must empower one another to all get involved in the industry to succeed, regardless of statistics and gender politics.

this would help make permanent positive changes in the music industry and the world we live in by causing awareness. let‚Äôs achieve this by supporting one another in order to provide equal opportunities within the music industry and by providing a healthy workplace for all future workers! ‚≠êÔ∏è

text_retweet:
well worded message.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
reposting @stefani.ruper: ‚†Ä
...‚†Ä
"a hard question that needs to be asked:‚†Ä
‚†Ä
hetero ladies: do you care about consent and want the men in your life to always respect your boundaries? and: do you also find it unsexy if a man asks if he can kiss you? if you answered yes to both questions, you're being hypocritical, and a part of the problem. i hesitate to use such strong language, but it's simply true. men are under two very strong and very contradictory pressures in society today: on one hand, to be good feminists who care about #metoo, and on the other hand, to hold up the stereotypical manly role of initiating physical contact without "ruining the moment." this is a literally impossible position to be in. can you imagine the confusion and pressure? ‚†Ä
the thing about gender relations and norms is that women can be part of the problem, too. we can reinforce harmful behaviors and stereotypes, too. if we want to reform gender relations for the better, then it's our obligation not just to analyze, critique, and reform others, but also ourselves. contrary to what many women tell me, it is not impossible to change what you're into. it really isn't. it just takes introspection. it takes deconstructing your biases. it takes looking at things you had previously ignored because society told you to (e.g., gentle men, communicative men) in a new, appreciative light. and maybe you don't want to change what you're into, but that requires honesty with yourself and others and communication, too. in today's world it is only fair that we make it clear what we want from and with the men in our life. so shall we do some digging and get to work? üîßüîßüîß #consentculture #metoo #feminism #genderrelations #whatwomenwant #unpopularopinion"

a young lady surfer has been left speechless today after a group of men allowed her catch a set wave while surfing her local break.the female, who is usually only allowed to have the scraps on the inside that none of the men want, was in awe as she paddled into the wave without being hassled or dropped in on by a man.‚Äúyeah i consider myself a bit of a feminist‚Äù said one of the local males who gave her permission to catch the wave, ‚Äúi love chicks. why shouldn‚Äôt we let her have a wave. in this day and age with all the #metoo‚Äôs and that, chicks should be allowed to vote and stuff. plus the wsl is paying them the same as the fellas so if its good enough for mr ziff then its good enough for me.‚Äùthe female received plenty of positive reviews of her ride on the way back out with one spectator saying ‚Äúshe surfs pretty good for a chick‚Äù and another 60 year old longboarder giving her tips on how to improve her bottom turn.the luck of the young gurfer changed soon after as a ‚Äúlocal‚Äù who has been surfing for 25 years and still can't do a re-entry, paddled out and proceeded to burn her multiple times, sending her back to the inside for the rest of the session.

text:
i know i‚Äôve said this before, but it‚Äôs so important - men are vulnerable. we‚Äôre taught that we‚Äôre not supposed to be, but we are. we‚Äôre vulnerable to heartache, mental illness, trauma, and so on. but male vulnerability is often equated with weakness, which in turn is associated with shame. so why would a man decidedly make himself vulnerable to get the help he needs? how does a man know when vulnerability is no longer a weakness but a strength? that shame associated with being vulnerable plays a big role in why suicide is the leading cause of death in men under 50. it‚Äôs time we break through the barriers of shame for ourselves and for the next generation who watches us so closely. seek the help you need; you can start with a visit to your general practitioner, contacting your insurance company to see what mental health services are covered by your plan, or getting online to research what low-cost clinics are in your nearby area. there are also countless hotlines waiting to help, all of which can be found with a quick google search (many are regional and can direct you to local resources). get plugged in! and if you suspect a man in your life is struggling with mental health issues, approach him and share your concern. it could save his life!

text:
update on the lady who was assaulted by a group of men in edo state, nigeria. 
god bless nigeria for following up with this case of jungle justice. thanks to everyone who fought for this poor lady. üôèüèΩ
.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
official police statement 
in reply please quote 
ref no. cz.5300/fprd/fhq/abj/vol.2/5 
date: 7th february, 2019 
the director of news ‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶. ‚Äãpress release

re: viral video of indecent assault on a young nigerian lady * npf records breakthrough * arrest six (6) male suspects * pledges justice for the victim

operatives of the nigeria police force have arrested six male suspects involved in the shocking, barbaric and indecent assault meted out on a young nigerian female as shown in a video which recently went viral.

following the dehumanizing incident, the inspector general of police, igp mohammed adamu had ordered a comprehensive investigation into the report.

consequently, the edo state police command, led by its commissioner of police, cp hakeem odumosu swung into action, leading to the investigative breakthrough.

two other male suspects are still at large. efforts are being intensified to arrest them and bring all involved to justice.

the nigeria police force condemns jungle justice in its entirety and warns of dire consequences for persons who resort to criminal acts of self-help.

text:
on january 9th, 2019, the new york senate introduces a bill titled the ‚Äúreproductive health act‚Äù. it is important to note that, prior to this act, abortions were very restricted after 24 weeks, or the second trimester of pregnancy. this act was not an entirely new bill, but it was instead an amendment to the old new york abortion laws. the changes made include: the legalization of abortion ‚Äúat any time when necessary to protect a women‚Äôs life or health‚Äù, the allowance of medical professionals who are not doctors to perform abortions, and the repealing of criminal charges for harming unborn children. (source for this part of the info: https://www.nysenate.gov/legislation/bills/2019/s240)
______________________________________________________
supporters of the bill said that it was necessary for these changes to be made to protect the reproductive right of women who want to have abortions in case roe v. wade was overturned (source: https://buffalonews.com/2019/01/22/long-stalled-abortion-bill-passes-new-york-legislature/). supporters also claim that the bill was needed to take abortion out of the state criminal codes and make it public health law instead (source: https://wqad.com/2019/01/25/how-new-yorks-abortion-law-has-changed/) deniers of this bill claimed that the wording of the bill, specifically the part that allows for abortion ‚Äúat any time when necessary to protect a women‚Äôs life or health‚Äù claim that this vague wording allows for abortions to happen up until moments before the baby is born (source: https://buffalonews.com/2019/01/22/long-stalled-abortion-bill-passes-new-york-legislature/). another complaint of deniers of the bill was that, if a fetus was killed because of an assault on a women, that person could now not be prosecuted due to the repeal of criminal charges for harming unborn fetuses (source: https://www-m.cnn.com/2019/01/23/health/new-york-abortion-measures-trnd/index.html?r=https%3a%2f%)
_____________________________________________________
after seeing this info, what are your opinions on the new new york abortion laws? feel free to tell us below ‚§µÔ∏è

text:
are things at home feeling a bit disorderly?

i urge families to find the routine that models the behaviors you want to see. it‚Äôs tough at first but it will work if you‚Äôre true to your family‚Äôs lifestyle. everybody‚Äôs family is different. seeing my girls just fall in line this morning is a win for many reasons, but if any it‚Äôs a testament of perseverance and patience. üíñ üôèüèæüôåüèæ when we first started homeschooling i was very disorganized. mostly because i didn‚Äôt know what i was supposed to be organizing. my daughter had a love for learning early on in her development she was so curious and eager to explore the world around her. 
it was a constant challenge to keep her stimulated with toys and activities she enjoyed. it wasn‚Äôt until we decided to homeschool and tailoring her teachings to her interest thy we saw improvement. the energy around schools ignores everything‚Äôs else we do in our day and we take our daily routine seriously we‚Äôve saw progress in emotional stability and concentration on i trusted tasks especially with my toddler. 
modeling the behavior day in and day our girls have positive habits to lead and to mimic. as a result my stress and anxiety has gone done significantly, trying to juggle my attention between my girls, my self and their dad has taken its tile at time, but we are loving this rhythm. everyone has a role and we work together as a team. 
#keepworkingonit

text:
the accusation against justin fairfax resurfaced over the weekend after democratic gov. ralph northam faced calls for resignation following the discovery of a racist photo on his medical school yearbook page. 
vanessa tyson, a professor at scripps college, publicly identified herself as fairfax's accuser on wednesday and released a lengthy statement detailing her version of events.

tyson said fairfax forced her to perform nonconsensual oral sex at the 2004 democratic national convention.

sen. kamala harris of california told reporters thursday that tyson's statement "reads as a credible account" and called for an investigation into the incident.

sen. cory booker of new jersey, another 2020 candidate, told cnn the allegation was "deeply, deeply disturbing" and praised tyson for coming forward. he, too called for an investigation.

sen. kirsten gillibrand of new york praised tyson's courage wednesday night on podcast "lovett or leave it," saying that her account is credible and disturbing and warrants investigation.
.

text: book 7: beartown by fredrick backman. this book absolutely blew me away. it‚Äôs a story about a small hockey town in the middle of a forest fighting for survival. they rely on their team to win- because if they do, they‚Äôll bring in sponsors and schools and commerce. but treating these kids like gods carrying the weight of their town‚Äôs livelihood on their shoulders comes at a price. it all blows up, the lines between right & wrong are blurred, and this book, which is about a hockey town, becomes way more than that. it‚Äôs about friendship and pride and the things parents will do for their kids and about believing victims and holding your values tight. beartown is beautifully written, the prose so gorgeous that it took me twice as long to read because i kept stopping to soak it in. this book couldn‚Äôt be more relevant than right now, as we wade through the thick of the #metoo movement. this is a book that should be taught in high school. i highly recommend reading, even if hockey isn‚Äôt your thing- because i promise, it‚Äôs about so much more than that.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate‚Ñ¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin

text:
but wylie wasn‚Äôt just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: ‚Äúinformation operations‚Äù, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military‚Äôs doctrine of the ‚Äúfive-dimensional battle space‚Äù. his brief ranged across the scl group ‚Äì the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as ‚Äúmi6 for hire‚Äù, and i‚Äôd never quite understood it.
.
- it‚Äôs like dirty mi6 because you‚Äôre not constrained. there‚Äôs no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it‚Äôs normal for a ‚Äòmarket research company‚Äô to amass data on domestic populations. and if you‚Äôre working in some country and there‚Äôs an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that‚Äôs just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it‚Äôs one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‚Äòoh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.‚Äô
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer ‚Äì the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates ‚Äì and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
today i was notified that justice was served!!! my sweet friend was strong, powerful, talented, beautiful and fierce, she was a mommy and an entrepreneur and she deserved the world but her world was cut short by a weak ass, jealous man. today the man that was supposed to love her will remain locked behind bars where he belongs. justice!!!! i want to leave you all with this. your partner should empower you, not de-power you!!! he/she should add strength to who you are, be a source of healthy energy. if it‚Äôs taking life from you and only draining you, get rid of it!!! no matter what it is!!!! your man, your woman, your friend, your business, i don‚Äôt give a shit what, if it‚Äôs not serving you well let it go, in fact open the door and kick its ass out. life is way to short & fragile to ever give your life power to another. if you don't know how you can leave those unhealthy relationships, please message me whether we know each other in real life or not i'm here! this isn't the only tragedy of domestic violence i've personally come across in my life and even typing these words i feel nauseous. trust me, there's help you just need to do the first step and tell someone you're in a bad situation. i love you amber kay, your story will never die!!!! till we see each other again üíã

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
ca now celebrates black history &  power leaders: 
we are seizing the opportunity to honor the too-often neglected accomplishments of black americans in every area of endeavor.  the month of february is set aside to serve as a  powerful reminder that we stand on the shoulders of greatness. we are reminded this is not a race but a relay. we remain committed to intersectional gender equity, honoring our past and developing new leaders. join us in celebrating our political, cultural, and social transformational leadership.

on this day, we honor tarana burke! share this post to celebrate this civil rights activist and her incredible contributions to black culture/politics, as well as the #metoo movement. #powerleaders #nowtrendsetters.

text:
today is a day to ‚Äòshine a light on human trafficking‚Äô.
.
my hands have hugged women and children who‚Äôve survived human trafficking and sexual exploitation in america and overseas. my hands have told johns who were trying to purchase me no. my hands have shaken as i testified at the massachusetts state house against trafficking. my hands have called emergency hotline numbers with a woman while on a beach vacation. my hands have played board games with children rescued from a cybersex ring in the philippines. and my hands have prayed for so many still in hiding.
.
this is an issue near to my heart. there are over 40 million being trafficked today and many in our own backyards. today your hands could bring awareness to one of the biggest issues of our time. just draw a red x and take the opportunities to tell people about modern day slavery and the #enditmovement. #inittoendit‚ùå
.
‚Äúspeak up for those who cannot speak for themselves; ensure justice for those being crushed. yes, speak up for the poor and helpless, and see that they get justice.‚Äù proverbs 31: 8-9

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn‚Äôs don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica‚Äôs parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan‚Äôs app may not have been completely deleted. kogan‚Äôs app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
dems accused of metoo hypocrisy in virginia
#
democrats in washington are fighting gop allegations of hypocrisy over the political maelstrom roiling their party in virginia.the accusations come just months after national democrats, near the height of the #metoo movement, demanded brett kavanaughbrett michael kavanaughfairfax retains kavanaugh's firm amid allegations virginia in tumult as top democrats engulfed in controversy fairfax accuser says consensual situation 'quickly turned into a sexual assault' more abandon his supreme court nomination following allegations he had sexually assaulted a teenage girl when he was in high school.republicans are now focusing on how democrats have stopped short of calling for the resignation of virginia lt. gov. justin fairfax (d), who is facing similar allegations surrounding an incident also said to have occurred¬†many years ago.many capitol hill democrats are holding their fire and urging virginia state officials to conduct an investigation.the juxtaposed episodes ‚Äî and the contrasting responses ‚Äî are creating headaches for democrats in richmond and washington; testing the party‚Äôs zero-tolerance policy when it comes to sexual harassment charges, regardless how old; and prompting charges from across the aisle that democrats are applying a double standard purely to protect one of their own.democrats ‚Äúhave not really been saying, ‚Äòhe‚Äôs got to go. he‚Äôs got to‚Ä¶

text: this poem resembles some of what us survivors have to overcome. being sexually abused takes a part of you. for most people, it tears them apart. our peace is interrupted. we try to find ways to heal ourselves but struggle greatly doing so. trusting others becomes difficult and can even cause us to build walls. many of us believed that we were the ones to blame. when we try to move forward, at some point we have thought that we are not worthy or even questioned ourselves, ‚Äúwho would even want to be with a person like me?‚Äù we have thought that we are not in control because we have all experienced some sort of act of being powerless. before i shared my story, for many years i felt as if i was the only one that had gone through this experience. now that i have opened up to others, many have opened up to me. some were strangers and some were those that i have known very well. if you are a survivor, i am here to listen and learn from your experience. comment below or dm me if you can relate to this poem or if you‚Äôre willing to share your story. also follow my other page for more @lifeofanovercomer ‚ù§Ô∏è #savethechildren #childabuseawareness #healing #lovewins #growth #lifeofanovercomer #metoo #timesup #mystory #speakup #poems #quotes #mentalhealth #journey #sexualabuse #breakthesilence #livelife #nolongeravictim #support #youarenotalone #truth #strong #trauma #womensrights

text:
http://soundcloud.com/armaan-malde/surviving

the aftermath of childhood abuse is complicated. there's this devastating knowledge that someone has purposefully hobbled you, stolen away developmental milestones that help healthy people relate to one another, build love and trust and friendship. because me finding a real family would have threatened her kingdom.

i got away, but now i'm left to repair the damage. i've grappled with myself day in and day out, is it worth it? a constant struggle between the dream life i've created for myself that i still can't feel present in, and the relief of death. 
i can't really describe the feeling of making that choice so many times. sometimes the things i can't express in words come out in song instead. when they tried to cut me off from everything that could save me, when they tried to choke off my voice, they failed. i may not be able to talk sometimes but i can sing. 
oh yeah link is in my bio if you want something easily clickable ‚úåÔ∏è #survivor #metoo #singersongwriter #munchausenbyproxy #childhoodabuse #ftm

text: my favorite thing about this photo is that my dad made this shirt. text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign‚Äôs use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people‚Äôs profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there ‚Äúcould have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating‚Äù. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday‚Äôs hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

strangulation....the leading cause of traumatic brain injury #tbi in the us?! it's hard to get back to yourself after this happens to you. trauma changes everything especially feeling safe in your own skin. i've never appreciated or focused on my brian health before this happened now i go to great lengths to protect and heal my brain and it does heal! i mean you are not ever exactly the same but you do heal if you work at it. if this happens to you, you must report it! if you survived you got lucky because it's no different if the weapon was a gun. multiple times will severely injure your brain!

text_retweet:
kita masih agni & tidak akan menyerah

#repost @pikiranlelaki_
‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢ ‚Ä¢
ya, kata "damai" itu tidak pernah terucap dari mulut agni, melainkan ia diucapkan secara serampangan oleh mulut kaum patriarki.
.
agni tidak menyerah, agni tidak berdamai. semua dilakukan karena berbagai macam pertimbangan. apapun realitanya, kini kita harus mengelus dada, mendapati negeri ini masih belum mampu menyelesaikan masalah kekerasan seksual dengan baik.
.
kita juga tentu marah, menyadari bahwa kita masih belum dapat bergerak bebas dengan aman dan damai di lingkungan kita sendiri. para pelaku kekerasan seksual tentu masih bebas bergentayangan menghantui kita semua, karena pada akhirnya mereka tidak akan mendapatkan hukuman apapun selain pemakluman.
.
dan korban? kita juga mesti menangis melihat fenomena victim blaming masih menjadi hal yang dianggap harus dilakukan.
.
